WEBVTT

1
00:00:13.681 --> 00:00:15.601
<i>Commander. do you have
eyes on the target?</i>

2
00:00:15.625 --> 00:00:17.249
Barely. It's moving fast.

3
00:00:17.333 --> 00:00:20.416
<i>You are free to engage. We cannot
allow it to enter U.S. airspace.</i>

4
00:00:20.500 --> 00:00:21.874
Copy that. Weapons hot.

5
00:00:21.958 --> 00:00:23.278
Fire at will.

6
00:00:30.368 --> 00:00:32.749
Contact! The object's
hit. It's going down.

7
00:00:32.833 --> 00:00:33.833
<i>Where?</i>

8
00:00:34.954 --> 00:00:36.582
<i>♪ Waiting for a star to fall ♪</i>

9
00:00:37.750 --> 00:00:39.999
<i>♪ And carry your ♪
♪ heart into my arms ♪</i>

10
00:00:40.083 --> 00:00:41.999
<i>♪ That's where you belong ♪</i>

11
00:01:06.833 --> 00:01:07.999
What the...

12
00:01:08.024 --> 00:01:09.690
Is that a kid?

13
00:01:09.715 --> 00:01:12.464
Not just any kid.
but Peter Quill.

14
00:01:12.666 --> 00:01:16.374
A son of Earth and the
stars whose pain and loss

15
00:01:16.399 --> 00:01:20.440
now threatens to destroy the
very world he once called home.

16
00:01:20.465 --> 00:01:23.583
And the entire
universe along with it.

17
00:01:34.590 --> 00:01:35.729
<i>Time.</i>

18
00:01:39.007 --> 00:01:40.007
<i>Space.</i>

19
00:01:41.750 --> 00:01:42.750
<i>Reality.</i>

20
00:01:45.743 --> 00:01:47.619
<i>It's more than a linear path.</i>

21
00:01:52.068 --> 00:01:57.078
<i>It's a prism of
endless possibility.</i>

22
00:01:59.262 --> 00:02:02.887
<i>where a single choice can branch
out into infinite realities.</i>

23
00:02:05.486 --> 00:02:08.521
<i>creating alternate worlds
from the ones you know.</i>

24
00:02:12.184 --> 00:02:13.946
<i>I am the Watcher.</i>

25
00:02:16.001 --> 00:02:19.085
<i>I am your guide through
these vast new realities.</i>

26
00:02:20.673 --> 00:02:24.340
<i>Follow me and ponder
the question...</i>

27
00:02:27.820 --> 00:02:29.236
<i>"What if?"</i>

28
00:02:35.842 --> 00:02:37.207
<i>Six months earlier.</i>

29
00:02:37.291 --> 00:02:42.083
<i>the Ravagers were dispatched to abduct
Peter Quill from his home world.</i>

30
00:02:43.763 --> 00:02:47.124
<i>But young Quill's captor couldn't
bring himself to turn him over</i>

31
00:02:47.208 --> 00:02:49.874
<i>and chose to raise
him as his own.</i>

32
00:02:49.958 --> 00:02:53.000
<i>At least. that's how
the story often goes.</i>

33
00:02:53.541 --> 00:02:57.916
<i>But in this universe. Yondu
never had his change of heart.</i>

34
00:02:58.291 --> 00:03:04.291
<i>So he turned Peter over to his father.
the Celestial being known as Ego.</i>

35
00:03:04.625 --> 00:03:07.708
Well. you won't be needing
these anymore. Peter.

36
00:03:12.916 --> 00:03:16.138
Not when there's so much
more for you to play with.

37
00:03:16.163 --> 00:03:18.541
<i>Ego called it the Expansion.</i>

38
00:03:18.566 --> 00:03:22.940
<i>a long-held dream to remake
the universe in his image.</i>

39
00:03:22.965 --> 00:03:24.964
<i>And with his son
now at his side.</i>

40
00:03:24.989 --> 00:03:28.839
<i>he had all the power he needed
to bring it to fruition.</i>

41
00:03:32.980 --> 00:03:35.285
<i>Orbital Intelligence
has retraced his steps</i>

42
00:03:35.310 --> 00:03:37.416
across dozens of
nearby solar systems.

43
00:03:37.500 --> 00:03:40.800
all destroyed. consumed by
a wave of cosmic radiation

44
00:03:40.825 --> 00:03:42.283
within 24 hours of his arrival.

45
00:03:42.308 --> 00:03:44.285
And I thought my kid
was a pain in the ass.

46
00:03:44.310 --> 00:03:45.351
Tony has spunk.

47
00:03:45.376 --> 00:03:48.917
This kid has an entire nuclear
arsenal coursing through his veins.

48
00:03:48.942 --> 00:03:50.377
With that kind of firepower.

49
00:03:50.402 --> 00:03:52.762
I don't know that there's a
person on Earth who can stop him.

50
00:03:52.786 --> 00:03:55.342
Not one person working
alone. but a team.

51
00:03:55.367 --> 00:03:57.824
made up of the best our
little planet has to offer.

52
00:03:57.849 --> 00:03:59.849
You forgetting we're in
the middle of a Cold War?

53
00:03:59.874 --> 00:04:04.665
All that <i>We Are the World</i> garbage
doesn't really play outside of MTV.

54
00:04:04.836 --> 00:04:07.252
This boy has already torn
through midtown Manhattan

55
00:04:07.277 --> 00:04:08.641
in a matter of minutes. Howard.

56
00:04:08.666 --> 00:04:13.041
At the rate he's going. our planet
won't last a day. We need help.

57
00:04:14.818 --> 00:04:17.096
Okay. Who's on our roster?

58
00:04:19.375 --> 00:04:22.624
Um. there's no vegetable.

59
00:04:22.708 --> 00:04:25.750
The potato chips
are the vegetable.

60
00:04:26.429 --> 00:04:27.650
Seriously?

61
00:04:29.208 --> 00:04:33.833
- And you're supposed to be a scientist?
- And you're supposed to like potato chips.

62
00:04:44.883 --> 00:04:46.924
<i>Hank. please don't hang up.</i>

63
00:04:52.250 --> 00:04:55.332
You know. for a genius. Stark.
you're pretty slow on the take.

64
00:04:55.416 --> 00:04:57.582
<i>Listen. if you don't wanna
talk to me. that's fine.</i>

65
00:04:57.666 --> 00:04:59.958
<i>Just do one thing.
Turn on the TV.</i>

66
00:05:00.083 --> 00:05:02.526
- What?
- Dad? You should see this.

67
00:05:02.551 --> 00:05:04.736
<i>Grand Central Terminal
and parts of Midtown.</i>

68
00:05:04.761 --> 00:05:06.375
<i>The aircraft's
occupant was seen...</i>

69
00:05:07.054 --> 00:05:08.470
Send the plane.

70
00:05:08.495 --> 00:05:10.077
<i>One step ahead of you.</i>

71
00:05:12.163 --> 00:05:14.121
Typical.

72
00:05:14.695 --> 00:05:17.323
Hey. honey. You wanna
go to work with Dad?

73
00:05:21.000 --> 00:05:23.916
Whoa! This is where you work?

74
00:05:24.041 --> 00:05:28.625
No. no. Used to work.
sweetie. Not anymore.

75
00:05:30.008 --> 00:05:32.374
This is so cool.

76
00:05:32.458 --> 00:05:35.124
Things must be real bad if they
had the balls to call us in.

77
00:05:35.208 --> 00:05:38.874
Foster. Great. Now I
know it's a disaster.

78
00:05:38.899 --> 00:05:41.857
Always a pleasure. What's the matter?
Didn't wanna spring for a sitter?

79
00:05:42.000 --> 00:05:46.499
You know damn well I don't have anyone
to leave her with. thanks to this place.

80
00:05:46.524 --> 00:05:48.982
Let's save the fighting for
the battlefield. shall we?

81
00:05:49.007 --> 00:05:51.141
Wow. Who's the guy in the armor?

82
00:05:51.166 --> 00:05:54.082
King T'Chaka of the
African kingdom of Wakanda.

83
00:05:54.107 --> 00:05:57.023
They don't typically involve
themselves in global affairs. but...

84
00:05:57.048 --> 00:05:59.475
- Aliens?
- Yes. aliens.

85
00:05:59.500 --> 00:06:01.234
Your Highness. it's a pleasure.

86
00:06:01.259 --> 00:06:03.641
Your father was a great
ally to us during the war.

87
00:06:03.666 --> 00:06:07.226
Yes. I understand he even donated
some Vibranium to your efforts.

88
00:06:07.251 --> 00:06:09.542
We made a shield out of it
and lost it in the Arctic.

89
00:06:09.567 --> 00:06:11.641
But other than that. things
turned out pretty well.

90
00:06:11.666 --> 00:06:13.642
Hey. how'd the Commies
snag an invite?

91
00:06:13.667 --> 00:06:17.167
Gorbachev wanted the target
contained before he reaches Moscow.

92
00:06:17.192 --> 00:06:21.775
So he sent the Winter Soldier.
the world's most deadly assassin.

93
00:06:26.801 --> 00:06:31.808
It looks just like him.
Howard. Just like Bucky.

94
00:06:31.833 --> 00:06:32.812
I'd heard the rumors.

95
00:06:32.837 --> 00:06:36.836
But even if they're true. the
man we knew is long gone. Peg.

96
00:06:36.992 --> 00:06:38.791
And we have bigger fish to fry.

97
00:06:43.560 --> 00:06:46.434
Satellites indicate an alarming
rate of cosmic radiation

98
00:06:46.459 --> 00:06:48.334
emanating from the
hostile's path.

99
00:06:48.429 --> 00:06:50.678
He's on the move. heading
towards Coney Island.

100
00:06:50.703 --> 00:06:52.702
And if we don't get there
and take him out now.

101
00:06:52.727 --> 00:06:55.893
the entire Eastern Seaboard won't be
inhabitable for the next half century.

102
00:06:55.923 --> 00:06:58.131
Are we even gonna be able
to intercept him in time?

103
00:06:58.156 --> 00:07:00.625
New York's a long way
from the Mojave Desert.

104
00:07:00.650 --> 00:07:04.108
- Not in my ride.
- Dr. Wendy Lawson. U.S. Air Force.

105
00:07:04.133 --> 00:07:06.757
She's spearheading our joint
research into the Tesseract.

106
00:07:06.782 --> 00:07:09.999
That uniform doesn't
really look like air force.

107
00:07:10.083 --> 00:07:12.166
It's not. It's Kree Starforce.

108
00:07:12.906 --> 00:07:15.531
- What?
- Long story. I'll explain on the way.

109
00:07:15.833 --> 00:07:18.749
Great. We got a Cat Man.

110
00:07:18.833 --> 00:07:20.541
Space Broad. Giant Man.

111
00:07:20.566 --> 00:07:22.782
Silent But Deadly.
Good to see you.

112
00:07:22.807 --> 00:07:26.445
- And you're gonna be the crusty guy.
- I was just saying...

113
00:07:26.470 --> 00:07:29.554
Buckle up. Crusty. This bird's
kind of a kick in the pants.

114
00:07:38.791 --> 00:07:40.875
This kid puts on quite a show.

115
00:07:43.520 --> 00:07:44.687
Hmm?

116
00:07:53.930 --> 00:07:56.875
<i>Dunk a duck. win a prize!</i>

117
00:07:57.453 --> 00:08:00.038
<i>Dunk a duck. win a prize!</i>

118
00:08:00.063 --> 00:08:03.062
From my perch. he does not
look all that threatening.

119
00:08:03.173 --> 00:08:04.900
<i>Looks can be deceiving.
Your Highness.</i>

120
00:08:04.924 --> 00:08:07.205
<i>You'd think the leader of
a technological superpower</i>

121
00:08:07.230 --> 00:08:10.021
<i>that masquerades as a Third World
country would appreciate that.</i>

122
00:08:11.817 --> 00:08:13.703
I see your point.

123
00:08:13.833 --> 00:08:15.541
<i>Lawson. how are we looking?</i>

124
00:08:15.566 --> 00:08:18.982
I'm at the crash site. Moving
in to secure the pod ship now.

125
00:08:19.007 --> 00:08:20.359
<i>Everybody in position?</i>

126
00:08:20.384 --> 00:08:22.301
Relax. I got the perimeter.

127
00:08:23.148 --> 00:08:24.814
<i>You've been juicing. Foster?</i>

128
00:08:24.839 --> 00:08:27.652
<i>I seem to remember you
maxing out at 21 feet.</i>

129
00:08:27.677 --> 00:08:30.676
<i>I made some adjustments. Hank. I
figured it's the end of the world.</i>

130
00:08:30.701 --> 00:08:32.172
<i>Go big or go home.</i>

131
00:08:32.197 --> 00:08:34.854
If you two are finished
measuring your statures.

132
00:08:34.879 --> 00:08:36.295
I have eyes on the target.

133
00:08:36.320 --> 00:08:39.444
He appears to be enjoying
himself on this tilt-a-whirl.

134
00:08:39.469 --> 00:08:40.946
<i>If you can isolate the kid.</i>

135
00:08:40.971 --> 00:08:43.221
<i>you should be able to trap
him in the photon grid.</i>

136
00:08:43.246 --> 00:08:45.870
You cover the trap.
I'll handle the boy.

137
00:08:45.895 --> 00:08:48.055
<i>Are you sure you do
not want any backup?</i>

138
00:08:48.080 --> 00:08:50.797
<i>No. I'm great with kids.</i>

139
00:08:51.125 --> 00:08:53.832
What's the matter. kid?

140
00:08:53.857 --> 00:08:56.492
- What?
- Something bugging you?

141
00:09:01.059 --> 00:09:03.619
<i>Okay. show time. Panther. get
ready with that tranquilizer.</i>

142
00:09:03.644 --> 00:09:05.725
Luring him to
your position now.

143
00:09:05.750 --> 00:09:07.500
I'll rendezvous
as soon as I can.

144
00:09:07.525 --> 00:09:10.438
This tech's advanced. It's gonna
take me a minute to crack it.

145
00:09:40.202 --> 00:09:44.076
Resistance will only make this
more difficult. my young friend.

146
00:09:53.041 --> 00:09:54.583
Well. that went poorly.

147
00:09:58.286 --> 00:09:59.286
I got him.

148
00:09:59.345 --> 00:10:01.511
Oh. no. No!

149
00:10:01.541 --> 00:10:03.082
Whoa!

150
00:10:03.251 --> 00:10:05.751
- Ha!
- Ahhh!

151
00:10:07.281 --> 00:10:08.541
Little help here.

152
00:10:11.982 --> 00:10:13.190
<i>Pull back. Killer.</i>

153
00:10:13.215 --> 00:10:16.048
If the Cube in that jet blows. there
won't be a planet left to save.

154
00:10:16.336 --> 00:10:17.336
Hyah!

155
00:10:33.507 --> 00:10:35.464
- Thanks. big guy.
- Anytime.

156
00:10:35.725 --> 00:10:37.100
Whoa!

157
00:10:37.125 --> 00:10:39.374
Guys. Problem child. 12 o'clock.

158
00:10:39.458 --> 00:10:41.082
Oh. no!

159
00:10:43.840 --> 00:10:45.400
Does anyone have a plan?

160
00:10:46.789 --> 00:10:49.008
I've got a plan. Retreat.

161
00:10:49.868 --> 00:10:51.399
Come on. people.

162
00:10:56.891 --> 00:10:58.625
Okay. let's go.

163
00:11:02.640 --> 00:11:05.181
Whoa! Aw. come on!

164
00:11:15.867 --> 00:11:17.075
Whoa!

165
00:11:23.525 --> 00:11:25.525
Who the hell is that guy?

166
00:11:26.609 --> 00:11:30.317
Wow. Is it really you?

167
00:11:30.429 --> 00:11:34.088
If you are referring
to your doom. then yes.

168
00:11:34.113 --> 00:11:38.155
Bummer. I thought you were
the dude from Van Halen.

169
00:11:40.041 --> 00:11:41.750
I'm... Van what?

170
00:11:43.470 --> 00:11:47.172
<i>Jotunheim was the first to
fall. Asgard soon thereafter.</i>

171
00:11:47.923 --> 00:11:52.382
<i>One by one. the armies of the Nine
Realms perished at that boy's hands.</i>

172
00:11:52.622 --> 00:11:56.289
Until this realm. Earth.
was all that remained.

173
00:11:56.765 --> 00:11:59.722
Well. surely. if you've come all this
way. you must have a plan in mind?

174
00:11:59.916 --> 00:12:01.250
The Celestial seedling.

175
00:12:01.345 --> 00:12:04.886
Ego has used them to implant his
essence on planets across the universe.

176
00:12:05.041 --> 00:12:08.649
I recovered Earth's on my way
here from a place called Missouri.

177
00:12:08.674 --> 00:12:11.840
So that's how he's doing it.
He's consuming these planets.

178
00:12:11.865 --> 00:12:16.739
The seedlings are the fuse of Ego's
Expansion. a fuse that must be lit.

179
00:12:16.846 --> 00:12:18.804
By the child. That
is why he is here.

180
00:12:18.829 --> 00:12:22.732
So. why don't we just shove this thing
down the garbage disposal? Problem solved.

181
00:12:22.757 --> 00:12:26.048
Wrong. The seedling is protected
by a veil of cosmic energy.

182
00:12:26.073 --> 00:12:28.989
Only a being of Celestial
origin can penetrate it.

183
00:12:29.133 --> 00:12:32.508
Well. lucky for us. we
have one in custody.

184
00:12:33.914 --> 00:12:38.384
<i>♪ - So if you're lost and on ♪
♪ your own -</i> ♪

185
00:12:39.145 --> 00:12:42.936
<i>♪ You can never surrender ♪</i>

186
00:12:43.083 --> 00:12:47.842
<i>♪ And when the night ♪
♪ is cold and dark ♪</i>

187
00:12:47.887 --> 00:12:51.803
♪ <i>- You can see...</i> <i>light ♪</i>

188
00:12:52.353 --> 00:12:53.520
Whoa!

189
00:12:56.559 --> 00:12:57.934
♪ <i>- To fight and... ♪</i>

190
00:12:57.958 --> 00:12:58.732
You know it.

191
00:12:58.757 --> 00:13:00.624
<i>♪ To never surrender ♪</i>

192
00:13:00.649 --> 00:13:02.357
<i>♪ To never... ♪</i>

193
00:13:02.382 --> 00:13:03.583
Come on.

194
00:13:04.661 --> 00:13:06.404
Nope? Just me?

195
00:13:07.701 --> 00:13:08.992
Kinda awkward.

196
00:13:09.017 --> 00:13:11.976
Cool song. though. It's always
been one of my mom's favorites.

197
00:13:12.124 --> 00:13:14.459
Or at least it was.

198
00:13:14.484 --> 00:13:17.411
- My mom loved it too.
- That her Walkman?

199
00:13:17.458 --> 00:13:18.499
Um...

200
00:13:18.524 --> 00:13:21.273
It's just. you're holding
on to it pretty tight.

201
00:13:21.298 --> 00:13:24.965
I know if I still had mine.
I'd probably be doing the same.

202
00:13:25.821 --> 00:13:30.737
You know. you don't seem so
bad. given where you're from.

203
00:13:30.762 --> 00:13:32.391
Hey. what's wrong with Missouri?

204
00:13:32.416 --> 00:13:36.041
Missouri? My dad said
you were an alien.

205
00:13:36.066 --> 00:13:39.107
Dude. feed me a corn dog
and call me Springsteen.

206
00:13:39.132 --> 00:13:40.923
because I was born in the U.S.A.

207
00:13:40.948 --> 00:13:44.449
Why else do you think I'd fly
10.000 light-years to get here?

208
00:13:44.474 --> 00:13:49.166
In a ship. by the way. with no tape
deck. I'm just trying to get home.

209
00:13:53.132 --> 00:13:55.892
Security breach in the
detainment facility.

210
00:13:58.049 --> 00:14:02.208
Where are my particles? And where's
Hope? And where's my key card?

211
00:14:06.291 --> 00:14:07.291
Whoa!

212
00:14:13.796 --> 00:14:15.962
And thank you. Dad.

213
00:14:17.481 --> 00:14:19.689
Whoa! That was crazy.

214
00:14:19.714 --> 00:14:24.057
I noticed a bus stop about a mile out. It
should get you to where you need to go.

215
00:14:24.082 --> 00:14:28.540
- And here. I want you to have this.
- What? No way. This was your mom's.

216
00:14:28.565 --> 00:14:33.981
Look. it's a long ride to Missouri.
and she'd be glad to know I'm sharing.

217
00:14:34.898 --> 00:14:36.685
Thanks. Hope.

218
00:14:37.497 --> 00:14:38.497
I owe you one.

219
00:14:38.522 --> 00:14:41.497
Hope! Come on. I think
they're down here.

220
00:14:42.041 --> 00:14:47.332
Oh! Hope. Thank God. You okay.
sweetie? Did he hurt you?

221
00:14:47.357 --> 00:14:50.443
Hurt me? Peter? He's
a kid. like me. Dad.

222
00:14:50.671 --> 00:14:52.753
I was just trying to
help him get home.

223
00:14:52.861 --> 00:14:57.138
- Home? Like his home world?
- No. like Missouri.

224
00:14:57.916 --> 00:15:02.083
You guys are making a mistake. Peter's
not behind all this. It's his dad.

225
00:15:02.130 --> 00:15:05.831
He says he's. like. a weird
alien space god or something.

226
00:15:05.856 --> 00:15:09.647
Yeah. Great. Blame the absentee father.
I get that enough from my own son.

227
00:15:09.672 --> 00:15:11.632
Sweetie. we really need
to find your friend.

228
00:15:11.657 --> 00:15:15.073
Did he say anything more specific
about where he might be headed?

229
00:15:15.122 --> 00:15:16.371
This is taking too long.

230
00:15:16.396 --> 00:15:19.459
I will find the boy and destroy
him and the seedling myself.

231
00:15:19.484 --> 00:15:22.419
Hey. Lightning Boy. we kind of
have a team thing going on here.

232
00:15:22.444 --> 00:15:25.600
And I have a duty thing
going on here. Mustache Man.

233
00:15:25.625 --> 00:15:28.207
To see to it that the boy
submits to Asgardian justice.

234
00:15:28.232 --> 00:15:30.565
Which entails what. exactly?

235
00:15:30.590 --> 00:15:33.423
Eternal flagellation.
impalement. some light maiming.

236
00:15:33.448 --> 00:15:34.794
You know. standard stuff.

237
00:15:34.819 --> 00:15:37.617
We can't just let you take
him. We need to study him.

238
00:15:37.642 --> 00:15:38.767
We need to kill him.

239
00:15:39.817 --> 00:15:43.400
- He's a threat. even without the seedling.
- Well. what do you know? He speaks.

240
00:15:43.425 --> 00:15:45.841
And who would've thought?
He's advocating murder.

241
00:15:45.866 --> 00:15:49.961
- It's a bit on the nose. if you ask me.
- Nevertheless. his logic is sound.

242
00:15:49.986 --> 00:15:52.891
So long as the boy lives. this
planet will never be safe.

243
00:15:52.916 --> 00:15:55.041
And is that not what
we're here to ensure?

244
00:15:55.066 --> 00:15:56.289
That's right.

245
00:15:56.314 --> 00:15:58.792
You're here to do
the right thing.

246
00:15:58.817 --> 00:16:01.700
And Peter deserves our
help as much as anyone.

247
00:16:02.723 --> 00:16:04.431
You want me to tell
you where he went?

248
00:16:04.456 --> 00:16:07.193
Then you have to promise
me you'll help him.

249
00:16:07.786 --> 00:16:09.703
You know that's what
Mom would've done.

250
00:16:15.239 --> 00:16:16.322
<i>Peter.</i>

251
00:16:17.111 --> 00:16:18.153
<i>Peter.</i>

252
00:16:20.132 --> 00:16:21.798
<i>Why can't he hear me?</i>

253
00:16:22.048 --> 00:16:24.589
Why can't I connect with my son?

254
00:16:24.614 --> 00:16:27.842
<i>According to his ship's logs.
the vessel was compromised</i>

255
00:16:27.867 --> 00:16:32.200
<i>by an enemy combatant before
sustaining catastrophic damage.</i>

256
00:16:32.806 --> 00:16:35.348
- Where?
<i>- Earth.</i>

257
00:16:36.000 --> 00:16:40.125
Well. then I guess I'll have to
finish what he started myself.

258
00:16:45.149 --> 00:16:48.125
Uh. Thunder Guy. is it
supposed to be doing this?

259
00:16:48.150 --> 00:16:51.191
The seedling is awakening.
Its master nears.

260
00:16:52.483 --> 00:16:57.357
We've got incoming. Another alien vessel
about to make landfall. right outside.

261
00:16:57.382 --> 00:16:58.708
Oh. man.

262
00:17:03.500 --> 00:17:06.832
Well. guess that's the
dad. The girl was right.

263
00:17:06.857 --> 00:17:09.315
Wouldn't I love to have
that printed on a T-shirt.

264
00:17:09.340 --> 00:17:11.714
We have our hands full with
just one of these Celestials.

265
00:17:11.739 --> 00:17:13.197
How are we gonna take on two?

266
00:17:13.222 --> 00:17:17.221
There is an ancient Wakandan proverb
from the days before our tribes united.

267
00:17:17.246 --> 00:17:21.829
"One only wins a two-front war by
getting out of your enemy's way."

268
00:17:21.919 --> 00:17:23.832
- Meaning?
- If you can't fight 'em both.

269
00:17:23.857 --> 00:17:24.898
let 'em fight each other.

270
00:17:24.923 --> 00:17:26.923
Lawson. tell me you
got eyes on that kid.

271
00:17:27.290 --> 00:17:31.013
<i>Picking up some cosmic radiation
that's definitely not of this world.</i>

272
00:17:31.106 --> 00:17:33.814
<i>You find him. you bring
him in ready to suit up.</i>

273
00:17:33.839 --> 00:17:35.088
<i>He may be our only hope</i>

274
00:17:35.113 --> 00:17:36.423
<i>of stopping dear old dad.</i>

275
00:17:36.447 --> 00:17:40.138
You really think a child is going to
be so willing to fight his own father?

276
00:17:40.163 --> 00:17:41.392
What?

277
00:17:41.417 --> 00:17:43.499
You're not a parent.
are you. Wendy?

278
00:18:07.622 --> 00:18:11.496
You've taken something
from me. I'd like it back.

279
00:18:11.521 --> 00:18:15.563
Not so long as there
is breath in my body.

280
00:18:17.697 --> 00:18:19.031
For Asgard!

281
00:18:27.278 --> 00:18:29.755
You got any breath
left in there. buddy?

282
00:18:29.780 --> 00:18:34.222
Hand over the seedling
and this will all be over.

283
00:18:34.247 --> 00:18:36.479
All this. meaning us?

284
00:18:36.504 --> 00:18:39.670
Not gonna happen. So if
you've come to destroy us.

285
00:18:39.695 --> 00:18:42.748
you're going to be leaving
here very disappointed.

286
00:18:42.773 --> 00:18:46.773
Destroy you? No. No. no.
no. I've come to save you.

287
00:18:47.474 --> 00:18:49.375
By growing and spreading.

288
00:18:49.400 --> 00:18:55.400
Covering all that exists.
until every part of you is me.

289
00:19:03.563 --> 00:19:05.378
You don't see that every day.

290
00:19:05.403 --> 00:19:06.664
Great.

291
00:19:06.689 --> 00:19:10.633
And if you will not give
us back what is ours...

292
00:19:12.054 --> 00:19:14.492
We will take it from you!

293
00:19:17.578 --> 00:19:18.619
Fire!

294
00:19:22.500 --> 00:19:23.578
Let's dance.

295
00:19:24.047 --> 00:19:25.421
Whoa!

296
00:19:36.036 --> 00:19:37.161
Incoming!

297
00:19:57.066 --> 00:19:59.399
- What?
- By Odin's beard!

298
00:20:05.922 --> 00:20:08.505
- Oh. I gotta go bigger.
- Take him out!

299
00:20:10.648 --> 00:20:13.689
We'll hold them off for as long as
we can. but Ego's forces are coming.

300
00:20:13.734 --> 00:20:15.525
<i>You need to get that
seedling out of there.</i>

301
00:20:15.562 --> 00:20:17.706
Sounds like a job for
our resident Terminator.

302
00:20:17.731 --> 00:20:19.689
Home Plate to Winter
Soldier. Do you copy?

303
00:20:21.169 --> 00:20:24.794
Winter Soldier. do you copy?

304
00:20:29.000 --> 00:20:30.000
Okay. Hank. look.

305
00:20:30.025 --> 00:20:32.414
I can use this gravitational
control to hold him down.

306
00:20:32.439 --> 00:20:34.090
but I'll need you to subdue him.

307
00:20:34.115 --> 00:20:36.323
We're dealing with an
8-year-old here. Lawson.

308
00:20:36.348 --> 00:20:39.485
We want him to help. we
have to make him want to.

309
00:20:40.083 --> 00:20:41.916
The Americans have
located the target.

310
00:20:41.941 --> 00:20:44.566
<i>Good.Are you ready to comply?</i>

311
00:20:45.630 --> 00:20:49.129
Hey there. kid. I'm
Hank. Hope's dad.

312
00:20:49.197 --> 00:20:51.197
She has told me a lot about you.

313
00:20:51.304 --> 00:20:54.886
Everything that's happening.
it's not me. it's him.

314
00:20:54.911 --> 00:20:58.328
He has this power to
get inside my head.

315
00:21:01.231 --> 00:21:02.564
What you got? What you...

316
00:21:02.666 --> 00:21:04.750
Oh!

317
00:21:04.976 --> 00:21:07.101
I can't...

318
00:21:08.914 --> 00:21:11.248
Come on. Let's go. Yeah!

319
00:21:13.663 --> 00:21:15.204
Come on!

320
00:21:17.703 --> 00:21:21.744
I thought maybe if I came back
here. I wouldn't feel so alone.

321
00:21:22.574 --> 00:21:27.574
But without my mom. it doesn't
even feel like home anymore.

322
00:21:28.041 --> 00:21:30.416
<i>You have the target in range.</i>

323
00:21:30.440 --> 00:21:31.673
<i>Shoot.</i>

324
00:21:31.697 --> 00:21:33.226
<i>Shoot.</i>

325
00:21:33.250 --> 00:21:35.210
- <i>Stand down. soldier.</i>
- Huh?

326
00:21:35.235 --> 00:21:37.259
<i>I intercepted your
handler's transmission.</i>

327
00:21:37.642 --> 00:21:39.205
It's just you and me. pal.

328
00:21:39.314 --> 00:21:40.750
There is no me.

329
00:21:42.017 --> 00:21:45.166
<i>Fall back! All units.
all units. fall back!</i>

330
00:21:47.297 --> 00:21:49.254
I know how you feel. Peter.

331
00:21:49.279 --> 00:21:52.945
Since we lost Hope's mom. our
home hasn't felt the same either.

332
00:21:53.072 --> 00:21:55.697
And to be honest.
neither have I.

333
00:21:55.937 --> 00:21:59.936
<i>The pain. the anger.
the loneliness.</i>

334
00:21:59.961 --> 00:22:03.210
<i>I know it can feel like you're
drowning in it. but I haven't.</i>

335
00:22:03.298 --> 00:22:04.757
<i>and you don't have to either.</i>

336
00:22:05.116 --> 00:22:08.324
so long as you let the people
around you pull you out.

337
00:22:08.700 --> 00:22:11.408
<i>Bucky. when you see that
kid. all you see is a target.</i>

338
00:22:11.433 --> 00:22:15.828
<i>But I see a future. The life he
can lead. the good he can do.</i>

339
00:22:15.853 --> 00:22:17.149
And I see it in you too.

340
00:22:17.174 --> 00:22:19.193
You don't know me.

341
00:22:19.223 --> 00:22:20.430
<i>Steve Rogers did.</i>

342
00:22:20.455 --> 00:22:25.477
<i>And the man he knew. the friend he
loved. would never take that shot.</i>

343
00:22:32.080 --> 00:22:33.844
We've got a big problem.

344
00:22:37.000 --> 00:22:38.708
Stark. are you seeing this?

345
00:22:39.390 --> 00:22:41.414
Howard. you have
hostiles inbound!

346
00:22:43.641 --> 00:22:46.930
Peter. come back
with us. Please.

347
00:22:46.958 --> 00:22:49.750
Come join our family.

348
00:22:51.947 --> 00:22:53.739
Bucky. please.

349
00:22:54.267 --> 00:22:56.844
Well. kid. what do you say?

350
00:22:59.250 --> 00:23:00.250
Bucky.

351
00:23:12.191 --> 00:23:14.308
<i>Hank. Lawson. Did
you get the kid?</i>

352
00:23:14.333 --> 00:23:15.500
Yeah. we got him.

353
00:23:15.525 --> 00:23:17.907
<i>- We need him back here now.</i>
- Roger that.

354
00:23:17.932 --> 00:23:22.348
Fifty years later. Captain
America is still saving my ass.

355
00:23:22.373 --> 00:23:24.516
<i>Repeat. the base has
been compromised.</i>

356
00:23:24.540 --> 00:23:26.624
<i>Get out of there!

357
00:23:29.941 --> 00:23:32.441
No! The seedling!

358
00:23:33.796 --> 00:23:36.546
If someone doesn't stop that
seedling. we are done for!

359
00:23:39.274 --> 00:23:42.333
- I can't break free.
- No!

360
00:23:43.931 --> 00:23:45.594
We're not gonna make it.

361
00:23:49.096 --> 00:23:52.220
Someone must stop it.

362
00:23:52.431 --> 00:23:54.431
- Yes!
- Oh. yeah!

363
00:23:54.523 --> 00:23:58.250
- As if on cue. Wendy!
- Crusty. jump.

364
00:24:07.345 --> 00:24:11.054
We got it! I hope you're
right about this. kid.

365
00:24:23.277 --> 00:24:25.819
Peter. You're alive!

366
00:24:25.844 --> 00:24:29.875
And you... Well. you seem to have
fallen in with the wrong crowd.

367
00:24:29.997 --> 00:24:31.788
This is my home. Dad.

368
00:24:31.813 --> 00:24:35.312
This is my mom's home. And I
can't just let you destroy it.

369
00:24:35.337 --> 00:24:37.295
That's the mortal in you. Peter.

370
00:24:37.320 --> 00:24:41.907
In time. though. you'll come
to understand everything dies.

371
00:24:42.533 --> 00:24:44.158
Except us.

372
00:24:44.356 --> 00:24:48.439
How could you say that? My
mother. you said you loved her.

373
00:24:48.464 --> 00:24:49.921
And that I did.

374
00:24:49.946 --> 00:24:52.687
But I knew if she were
to live. the Expansion.

375
00:24:52.712 --> 00:24:56.921
the reason for our existence.
would never come to pass.

376
00:24:57.525 --> 00:25:02.192
So I did what I had to do.
as you must now. Peter.

377
00:25:02.758 --> 00:25:04.916
You killed my mother?

378
00:25:04.941 --> 00:25:07.625
No. no. no. no. I
get it. You're upset.

379
00:25:07.650 --> 00:25:11.758
But you know you don't have
the power to destroy me. Peter.

380
00:25:11.966 --> 00:25:14.883
- You're right. But you do.
- Peter...

381
00:25:14.908 --> 00:25:18.938
And with this. a little bit of
you will always live inside of me.

382
00:25:19.414 --> 00:25:22.164
Deep down. I guess
I've always known

383
00:25:22.189 --> 00:25:24.597
you'd turn out to
be a disappointment.

384
00:25:24.622 --> 00:25:26.844
You are human after all.

385
00:25:26.869 --> 00:25:30.911
Actually. old man. my
mom says I'm a Star-Lord.

386
00:25:31.814 --> 00:25:33.044
Peter!

387
00:25:47.937 --> 00:25:50.687
Yes!

388
00:25:55.501 --> 00:25:56.501
Peter?

389
00:26:09.692 --> 00:26:12.845
It's a recipe. Hank. You're
not splitting the atom.

390
00:26:12.870 --> 00:26:16.119
To be honest. splitting the
atom is a lot more intuitive.

391
00:26:16.144 --> 00:26:19.166
This American libation is
surprisingly delicious.

392
00:26:19.191 --> 00:26:20.648
What do you call it?

393
00:26:20.673 --> 00:26:22.131
Uh. light beer?

394
00:26:22.177 --> 00:26:24.343
How exotic. Another!

395
00:26:24.368 --> 00:26:26.857
And this little
chicky's name is Goose.

396
00:26:26.882 --> 00:26:28.762
I thought maybe you kids
might like to have her.

397
00:26:28.787 --> 00:26:31.286
Thanks. but I'm more a dog guy.

398
00:26:31.311 --> 00:26:34.625
Peter. you don't say
no to a free cat.

399
00:26:34.650 --> 00:26:37.983
- Hey. any word on Silent But Deadly?
- He's in the wind.

400
00:26:38.008 --> 00:26:41.162
- That mean we should lock our doors?
- I don't think so.

401
00:26:41.187 --> 00:26:43.436
<i>Something broke through
that day in Missouri.</i>

402
00:26:43.461 --> 00:26:45.294
<i>The Winter Soldier
may be out there.</i>

403
00:26:45.319 --> 00:26:48.615
<i>but I'm pretty sure Bucky
Barnes is out there with him.</i>

404
00:26:52.619 --> 00:26:54.260
- Oh. that's funny.
- Yeah?

405
00:26:54.285 --> 00:26:55.874
- In Asgard.
- Yeah. exactly.

406
00:26:55.947 --> 00:26:57.475
Do you have similar pajamas?

407
00:26:57.500 --> 00:27:00.101
- Or do you go to sleep in your armor?
- And 53 gods is good.

408
00:27:00.125 --> 00:27:01.369
Okay. bucko.

409
00:27:01.416 --> 00:27:05.207
Many. many thanks to all of you
for this fine victory banquet.

410
00:27:05.232 --> 00:27:07.357
But I am afraid I must
bid thee farewell.

411
00:27:07.382 --> 00:27:10.332
Come on. What about
dessert? Hank burnt a pie.

412
00:27:10.357 --> 00:27:13.315
The boy may have destroyed
Ego's corporeal form.

413
00:27:13.340 --> 00:27:15.131
but his planet still lives.

414
00:27:15.156 --> 00:27:19.580
And the universe will not know peace
until I have avenged the ones we've lost.

415
00:27:19.605 --> 00:27:22.230
So. what. Thunder
brother? No invite?

416
00:27:22.305 --> 00:27:24.096
Perhaps you forgot. Goldilocks.

417
00:27:24.121 --> 00:27:27.565
we have sort of a team
thing going on here.

418
00:27:27.625 --> 00:27:30.688
Then I suggest
you suit up. team.
